During the course, students participating in the course carry out practical community development projects in small groups. Projects may be based on practical needs from partners and/or students' own ideas.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to give students the opportunity to initiate, further develop and / or implement practical development projects that support the well-being of the community with the knowledge and skills acquired during their studies.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student passing this course: * Associates the knowledge gained during the theoretical subjects with the practice of community development * Can initiate and / or implement projects that support the well-being of the community * Follows human rights, community well-being and community development values in the implementation of projects * Participates in the project team, analyzes the teamwork process and personal role in teamwork
